definitions.definition: One of the four competitions in a knockout tournament whose winners go on to play in the two semifinals .
A competition that narrows a field of contestants ( quarterfinalists ) to a set of semifinalists, for a subsequent final .

main_definition: ( sports ) One of the four competitions in a knockout tournament whose winners go on to play in the two semifinals .
